The paper deals with differential privacy, which is a topic in both data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on mean estimation suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. Additionally, the paper discusses the accuracy of the hybrid model, which involves a trusted curator, indicating that cryptography (cs.CR) may be relevant. Finally, the paper may also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it deals with privacy in data sharing.
